<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 3:50AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northwestern Smyth, Tazewell and southwestern Bland Counties through
430 AM EDT...
At 349 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Claypool Hill, or near Cedar Bluff, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Richlands...
Bluefield...
Tazewell...
Cedar Bluff...
Ceres...
Burkes Garden...
and Raven.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
